it is nice to teach and to tutor. it motivates me for the next lesson.

More of an educational place than a Cafe. However their muffins are great. I have heard the restaurant food is great too; but I have not tried it.

The program has motivated me and serves as a good pressure free avenue for self learning. A reward based system is a great tool for self improvement.

The pace is a bit slow but steady. I loved to listen to the stories and then find ways to narrate them in my own words.

Even though you need to pay for your coffee or drinks before graduation, I think it is reasonable.

It was a great experience and I would come again if I have the chance.

The trainers, staff and helpers are very friendly. I like the concept of getting the drinks first and then studying in English. For those who want to practice English in Malaysia, this is the best place to because the trainers always encourage and give advices.

I am happy and satisfied to be a volunteer here.
